The '''UK Museum of Ordure''' ('''UKMO''') was an online [[art]]s project initiated with the intention to explore the [[Curator|curatorial]] value of [[ordure]], or [[human waste]]. It consisted of a [[website]]<ref>{{cite web| url=http://museum-ordure.org.uk/ | title=UK Museum of Ordure | location=UK | accessdate=12 August 2015 }}</ref> which initially collected public submissions of ordure, as well as documenting various [[Installation art|installations]] undertaken by the museum. It has since been renamed '''Museum of Ordure'''<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.lesliensinvisibles.org/2011/10/ordure-finds-its-rightful-place-museum-of-ordure/ | title=Museum of Ordure | website=[http://www.lesliensinvisibles.org/ Les Liens Invisibles] | date=2011 | accessdate=12 August 2015 }}</ref> in recognition that its remit is international in scope.
Founded by Stuart Brisley, Geoff Cox and Adrian Ward in 2001, it now consists of the members Rosse Yael Sirb as Acting Director, as well as Maya Balgioglu, Stuart Brisely, Geoff Cox, and Les Liens Invisibles.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Speaking Code - Coding As Aesthetically Pleasing and Political Expression|last=Cox|first=Geoff|publisher=MIT Press|year=2013|isbn=978-0-262-01836-4|location=The MIT Press, 55 Hayward Street, Cambridge, MA 02142|pages=126|via=}}</ref>
It currently defines itself as follows:
